    "description": "If you're a passionate Visual Merchandiser with drive and ambition, Nippon Paint Store Holdings Services in Allahabad is the place for you. We're growing fast and need talented people to grow with us.\n\nAbout Nippon Paint Store Holdings Services:\nNippon Paint Store Holdings Services is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with the supply chain team for timely stock delivery\n• Manage shrinkage and reduce stock discrepancies\n• Manage store operations to ensure smooth daily functioning\n• Conduct regular stock audits and prevent pilferage\n• Prepare daily sales reports and share insights with management\n• Handle customer queries, complaints, and escalations effectively\n• Achieve sales targets and improve store performance metrics\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Sales Techniques\n• Proficiency in Shrinkage Control\n• Proficiency in Inventory Management\n• Proficiency in Retail Operations\n• Proficiency in Planogram\n• Proficiency in SAP Retail\n• Proficiency in Loss Prevention\n• Proficiency in Category Management\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Flexible working hours\n• Transportation and conveyance allowance\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Allahabad, Uttar Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Nippon Paint Store Holdings Services!",
